  "body": "**System information**\r\nErigon version: 2.29.0-dev-29b23895\r\n\r\n**OS & Version**\r\nUbuntu 22.04\r\n\r\n**Issue**\r\nAn OOM issue killed a fresh client sync at [7/16 Snapshots]. To resolve this, I increased swapfile size and decreased `batchSize`, and then restarted sync.\r\n\r\n**Notable Logs**\r\n```sh\r\n[WARN] \"..transactions.seg\": would have banned ... for touching piece xxxx after failed piece check\r\n# ...\r\n[1/16 Snapshots] download peers=...\r\n# ... some time later\r\n[1/16 Snapshots] DONE\r\n[2/16 Headers] Waiting for Consensus Layer...\r\n# ...\r\n# Then I seem to be stuck, and only getting the standard INFO logs\r\n[p2p] GoodPeers\r\n[txpool] stat ...\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Expected Behavior**\r\nSync to either start from cache (at 7/16 snapshots) OR to start from scratch, and resume past [2/16 snapshots]. Instead, I'm not sure what's happening/if I'm stuck. There are no more error/warn messages.\r\n\r\n**Questions**\r\n- Is the \"failed piece check\" warning related to my issue?\r\n- Do I need to clear cache somewhere to resume from 7/16 snapshots?\r\n- What can I read to truly understand snapshots, what's happening at each step, etc? \r\n\r\n\r\nThank you",
